Portugal's minority centre-rightgovernment was ousted in a parliamentary censure vote backed bythree left-wing opposition parties.    President Mario Soares, who returns from a visit to Brazilon Sunday, now faces the task of either forming a newgovernment or calling an early general election.    The Socialist Party, Democratic Renewal Party and CommunistParty, with 140 of the 250 parliamentary seats, voted for themotion against the ruling Social Democratic Party and itsChristian Democrat allies. Reuter&#3;